    <section class="tool-explainer">
      <h2>How to use the Loan Calculator</h2>
      <p>Enter the loan principal (the amount you are borrowing), the annual interest rate as a percentage, and the loan tenure in months or years. The calculator shows your monthly EMI, total interest paid over the life of the loan, and the total repayment amount.</p>

      <h2>How EMI is calculated</h2>
      <p>EMI uses the standard amortization formula: EMI = P &times; r &times; (1 + r)<sup>n</sup> &divide; ((1 + r)<sup>n</sup> &minus; 1), where P is the principal, r is the monthly interest rate (annual rate &divide; 12 &divide; 100), and n is the number of monthly payments. This formula accounts for compound interest applied to the decreasing outstanding balance each month.</p>
      <p><em>Disclaimer: Results are estimates only. Actual loan terms may differ based on lender policies, fees, and credit profile. Consult your lender or a financial adviser before making borrowing decisions.</em></p>

